minent peril.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWhaleszMexicozCalifornia, Gulf of. 0aWhales. 7aNATURE / Animals.2bisacsh  aaquatic mammals.  ablue whales.  acetacean researchers.  aconservationist.  acreatures.  adolphin tuna issue.  adolphins.  aecosystem.  aenvironmentalism.  agulf of california.  ahumpback whales.  amarine ecology.  amarine mammals.  amarine pollution.  amotherhood.  anets from bubbles.  anoise pollution.  aocean.  aoceanic creatures.  aopen ocean.  aoverfishing.  apersonal experiences.  aphenomenon.  asave the whales.  asocial networks.  asperm whales.  aswimming.  awhale sex.  awhales.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094221940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942219423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942219/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles